Everything Wrong With Spider-Man Far From Home
-Going basically as bad as Iron Man 3 did on Mandarin but somehow worse
I mean ok, I can come up with other complaints and none are anything to actually not like but,

Mysterio in this movie could've been terrifying, upped the ante insanely over spider-man's
first "self-defeated" villain from mcu movie 1, and showed the darker side of the spider-man world.
Instead they went for cheap thrills and and fake "effects" as well as "drones," not Mysterio with
true power. And again, cause Tony Stark did something wrong. They ran that garbage into the ground
by the time Age Of Ultron was released, and I'd hoped it stopped. Somehow it was ok in Homecoming, but again?
Do something original and don't destroy the next chosen villain, what a pile of crap.

snippet.textDisplay: I never liked the "Mysterio is an Iron Man Villain" angle that this movie created. With the Vulture there was a personal connection - Peter was in love with Adrian Toomes's daughter, and as a father Toomes liked Peter, but as a criminal Peter was in the way and had to go, so there was a mild conflict in the Vulture about straight up killing the nice boy his daughter liked, which resulted in him protecting Peter's name when given the chance to expose it. Mysterio doesn't have that connection at all. True, they sort-of bonded when Mysterio was running his con, but when they became enemies Beck had no qualms about killing Peter other than not liking the fact that he had to kill a kid. All of his hatred was geared toward Tony Stark, and it didn't have to be... in the comics Mysterio's first appearance had him dress up like Spider-man and cause crimes, then make his dramatic debut as Mysterio so he could catch Spidey and collect a reward. And the 90s animated series further added a personal touch by having Spider-man save Beck and a bunch of actors from a special effects explosion Beck rigged, making Beck get fired for causing the accident and Beck swearing revenge. Those two are pretty decent motivations for Mysterio, and would've made for a better movie than what we got. I don't hate this movie like I did with "Amazing Spider-man 2," but they really could've done better if they allowed Mysterio to be  SPIDER-MAN VILLAIN rather than an Iron Man villain who fought Spider-man in Tony's stead.
